This guide explains how to wire the ECG sensor module to your Arduino for proper data collection and signal logging.

Components Needed

Arduino board (e.g., Arduino Uno)

ECG sensor module

SD card module (optional, for logging data)

Jumper wires

Pin Connections

ECG Sensor Module to Arduino:

LO+ (Leads Off Positive) → Digital Pin 10

LO- (Leads Off Negative) → Digital Pin 11

Analog Output (ECG Signal) → Analog Pin A0

GND (Ground) → GND

VCC (Power Supply) → 3.3V or 5V (depending on your module)

SD Card Module to Arduino (if used):

CS (Chip Select) → Digital Pin 4 (or your preferred CS pin)

MOSI → Digital Pin 11 (on Uno)

MISO → Digital Pin 12 (on Uno)

SCK (Clock) → Digital Pin 13 (on Uno)

VCC → 5V

GND → GND

WIRING DIAGRAM:
ECG Module          Arduino
-------------------------------
LO+                D10
LO-                D11
Analog Out         A0
GND                GND
VCC                5V

SD Card Module     Arduino
-------------------------------
CS                 D4
MOSI               D11
MISO               D12
SCK                D13
VCC                5V
GND                GND
